There are incredible young people across Canada working tirelessly to find solutions to climate change and sustainably live and thrive with our natural ecosystems. We see these everyday heroes speaking at climate strikes, advocating for change to big businesses, encouraging people to change their lifestyle in subtle but impactful ways, and much more. These young people deserve recognition, which is why we created our Top 25 Environmentalists under 25 program nine years ago. We have annually celebrated Canada’s youngest minds that are working creatively and differently about how the way we work and live, and because of them, we’ve seen change for the better. Since 2011, this program:
Has celebrated over 200 environmental leaders across Canada, ranging from ages 8-25 and from every province and territory in Canada;
Contributed over $60,000 in cash awards and prizes to young leaders;
Connected dozens of leaders together to learn and grow from each other;
Partnered with over 50 organizations and media outlets to amplify the message of young leaders in Canada.
"As a young change-maker seeking to leverage my influence to drive environmental action, the Top 25 under 25 Award gave me the credibility, the recognition, and a platform to amplify my work, our vision, and principles. I was so grateful for being a two-time recipient of the award that I decided to give back by volunteering as a judge and later as Board Chair of the Starfish Canada." - Tesicca Truong, Top 25 finalistWhat’s happening In 2018, we received $100,000 from the Lawson Foundation to elevate and accelerate our work. The Lawson Foundation is taking a lead role in funding youth and environmental initiatives, and we are proud to be their partners in this endeavour. This year, they have decided to take the year to evaluate their progress in their 5th generation program, and as such, The Starfish Canada’s funding is paused for further consideration until that process is complete.Although we were unaware of this pause until recently, we are certainly supportive of evaluative processes — for us, that’s how we ensure we’re doing the right thing. Evaluative processes are essential to how we made important decisions about our Top 25 program over the years. The value of the work the Lawson Foundation will be undertaking can’t be understated and we are excited for what outcomes they get to.For our programming, it leaves us in a bind. With this current state of affairs and our major funder taking a pause, we are currently unable to provide the same level of support that we offered last year.  What we’re doingWe’re coming to you, our community of family, friends and supporters, to help us make sure our work can continue to do our best work. Please contribute what you can to help us make 2019 one of our best years yet.At The Starfish Canada, we believe in being as open and transparent as we can. Please note that We certainly are investigating various funding avenues to make this work continue. Our intent is that this is one of the multiple places where funding will help us do our best work, and the success of this campaign could help us secure additional funds in other places. We plan to determine when we will launch the 2019 iteration of this program after seeing how this campaign goes.Here are some of the other things we’ve done to make 2019 a great year:
We’ve applied for charitable status! This is a big step, as many funders and donors prefer to get tax receipts when they donate. Our application went out in March and we expect to hear back around September.
We have recruited a dedicated set of incredible volunteers as part of our leadership and editorial teams. These folks are essential to making our Top 25 programs and others a success.
“Being recognized in the Starfish Top 25 amplified my voice. The support and confidence I gained helped me to advocate for climate action to SFU’s board of governors. SFU recognized me for my sustainability work in the community, which opened the door to more opportunities including admission to a master’s program in mental health research.” - Raaj Chatterjee, Top 25 finalistWhat you getWe’ve lined up an amazing set of perks that you can grab. We know that giving can be a selfless act, and we want to promote giving through reciprocity. Anyone who donates can choose to become a member of The Starfish Canada. This gives you voting rights at our Annual General Meetings, discounts on our merchandise, and more. We’ve also worked with the kind folks at Coast Protein, earth’s choice, and others to provide valuable and sustainable gift packages (they sound delicious). Local artists have also stepped up to the plate to offer prints and original artwork to spruce up your home.We also have experiences to offer. We are offering sessions with a professional coach that can help you navigate through tough life obstacles in a confidential and creative manner.  If you’re looking to engage your community and want some assistance making an engagement plan for success, we have our co-founder who can guide you through how to make sure you meet the objectives you set out for you or your organization.
